be.signalsync.stream

Class MSPStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.signalsync.stream.MSPStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sliceable<float[],StreamSlicer>, Stream

    public class MSPStream
extends java.lang.Object
implements Stream
    This class makes it possible to use a sequence of MSPSignal object as a Stream. This only works if the maxPerformed method is called correctly.
    Author:
    Ward Van Assche

      • MSPStream

        public MSPStream(double mspSampleRate,
                 int mspBufferSize)
        Create a new MSPStream object. If the sampleRate in the config file is different from the Max/MSP sampleRate the stream will be resampled.
        Parameters:
        mspSampleRate - The sampleRate used in Max/MSP
        mspBufferSize - The bufferSize used in Max/MSP
